description.narrative:
&nbsp;
Overall goal of the CEJ&rsquo;s project is to establish a Sustainable, Greener and Cleaner development model for Sri Lanka via its objective to increase the awareness of the law makers on environmentally sustainable development and environmental good governance and to improve the civil society space in development decision making. As an output CEJ is expecting Five hundred law makers gained the knowledge on environmentally sustainable development and environmental good governance and 3000 current and future law makers received the toolkit on environmental sustainable development and good governance.
Several studies of CEJ has pointed out that, major development projects and other implementation have created major environmental and social problems. Therefore changing the development model by changing development thinking is crucial for achieving sustainable development. This can be only done by convincing the law-makers at all levels. Giving them a good understanding on the principles of development modelling in the resources scarce, crisis-facing world is a way forward to make those changes.
The project will target both male and female political leaders in all levels in all ages. However, we will target more on the political leaders at young age. CEJ is contributing to the Diakonia Socio Economic Justice intervention area and Sustainable Development and Climate Justice Results area&nbsp;
Political leaders are not directly accessible for further awareness and education therefor CEJ collaborate with another organisation or bodies who already have some ties with them. CEJ has previously worked with Federation of Sri Lankan Local Govt. Authorities who has this capability. They hope this strategy will allow them to reach the Politicians at the Provincial and Local government level. CEJ will collaborate with PAFFREL and TI also to reach out to the Parliamentarians further to their own contacts.
&nbsp;As an environmental organization CEJ addressed only environmental related issues and its main areas
